	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64374512"><p>&gt;space launches can launch from anywhere</p><p>This is actually not true in practical terms; the amount of energy required to make orbit varies considerably based on your distance from the equator and the direction you launch in.</p><p>Typically you want to be as close to the equator as you can manage and able to launch to the East with a lot of safe 'abort' territory under that flight path in case something goes wrong.</p></div>
	</div>

